H0.text: Meiosis is the process that begins with a diploid cell and ends with four haploid cells.

H1.text: Electrolysis is the process that begins with a diploid cell and ends with four haploid cells.

H2.text: Mitosis begins with a diploid cell and ends with four haploid cells.

H3.text: Urinalysis is what begins with a diploid cell and ends with four haploid cells.

A4.text: The diploid germ-line cells undergo meiosis to produce four haploid gametes.

A5.text: Mitosis is involved in the growth of diploid organisms, producing diploid cells.
